pe mapping.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering reification**\\n\\nI'm thinking about using `Array.newInstance` for reification to avoid encountering a `NoSuchFieldException`. It seems like a practical solution, as it allows me to create an array of a specific class type at runtime without dealing with the complexities of field access. This approach could streamline the process and help me avoid unnecessary reflection issues, which can complicate things. It feels like a solid choice for maintaining cleaner code.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Drn1zhhHKy5wlf8Xpn1w78ZH|fc_0f93eb1a3b21746b0169fc034fe2b881939b5cdc1bc56ac27a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/src/test/java/org_modelmapper/modelmapper/TypeResolverTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 687, "output": 882, "cacheRead": 39936, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41505, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778123586455, "responseId": "resp_0f93eb1a3b21746b0169fc034317c08193aabc6db3863bd0fd"}}
